# Goal Description
Create a Next.js application for a vocabulary learning app (Harvard 3000 words). Key features:
- Display vocabulary (word, type, example, etc.)
- User authentication and separation
- Ability to add new words
- A mini-game to review daily vocabulary in a fun way (e.g., Save the Princess from a Beast format).
- Use Supabase for database and auth
- Use Tailwind CSS and Shadcn-ui for premium aesthetics

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Supabase Configuration Needed**
> 1. You will need to create a project on Supabase (https://supabase.com).
> 2. Then provide the `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` to be placed in `.env.local`.
> 
> Also, could you confirm if you prefer **Shadcn UI** for the components, as it works excellently with Next.js and Tailwind? 

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [NEW] .env.local
For Supabase keys

#### [MODIFY] tailwind.config.ts / globals.css
Add modern, premium color palettes (e.g., sleek dark mode, vibrant accents) and animations for the mini-game.

### Database & Auth (Supabase)
#### [NEW] src/lib/supabase.ts
Initialize Supabase client.
Schema to be created in Supabase SQL Editor:
- `vocabularies` table (id, user_id, word, type, meaning, example, memorized, created_at)
- Row Level Security (RLS) to ensure users only see their own words

### UI Components & Features
#### [NEW] src/components/ui/*
Initialize Shadcn-ui components (Button, Input, Card, Dialog).

#### [NEW] src/app/login/page.tsx
Authentication page for logging in/registering.

#### [NEW] src/app/page.tsx
Dashboard. Show vocabulary list, add capability.

#### [NEW] src/app/minigame/page.tsx
Mini-game interface 'Save the Princess'.
Logic: Answer vocabulary flashcards correctly to attack the beast, answer wrong and the beast attacks.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
Currently not setting up Jest/Cypress. Verifying functional correctness on Next.js dev server.

### Manual Verification
1. `npm run dev` to start server
2. Go to `/login`, test user registration and login
3. Go to dashboard, add a vocabulary word. Verify it updates in Supabase and list.
4. Go to `/minigame` and test the interaction.
